  "texts": [
    "Kernberg et al. (2024) assessed not only the correctness of notes generated from ChatGPT 4, but also the reliability of its responses through three repeated runs for each input, although they did not alter model parameters to make the model more deterministic.",
    "In addition, they used standardized assessments rated by human experts to evaluate the quality of responses, without using automatic evaluation metrics.",
    "Aside from ChatGPT, we evaluate various open-weight and proprietary LLMs in generating clinical notes from provider-patient dialogues.",
    "Some studies (Atil et al., 2024; Savage et al., 2024; Yim et al., 2024) that evaluated LLM reliability also set model parameters that influence the determinism of LLMs, temperature, top_p and top_k, to a value of or close to 0 to make the model deterministic.",
    "We also set the model parameters to make them more deterministic."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Kernberg et al. (2024) assessed not only the correctness of notes generated from ChatGPT 4, but also the reliability of its responses through three repeated runs for each input, although they did not alter model parameters to make the model more deterministic.",
